What is a Categorical Variable?

A feature containing text categories instead of numbers.| Gender |
| ------ |  
| Male   |
| Female |

| Country   |
| --------- |
| Sri Lanka |
| India     |
| USA       |


Machine Learning algorithms cannot understand text values directly.

So we convert them into numbers using Encoding.


Independent Variable (X)
        ↓
OneHotEncoder

Target Variable (y)
        ↓
LabelEncoder

1. LabelEncoder
2. OneHotEncoder
3. ColumnTransformer

| Module            | Purpose                                          |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| LabelEncoder      | Convert target labels into numbers               |
| OneHotEncoder     | Convert categorical features into binary columns |
| ColumnTransformer | Apply transformations to selected columns        |
| fit()             | Learn categories                                 |
| transform()       | Convert data using learned categories            |
| fit_transform()   | Learn + Convert                                  |


Do we need Feature Scaling for Multiple Linear Regression?

Answer:

No. Multiple Linear Regression based on Ordinary Least Squares does not require feature scaling 
because coefficients are calculated analytically and are not affected by feature magnitudes.
| Algorithm                  | Scaling        |
| -------------------------- | -------------- |
| Linear Regression          | ❌ Not Required |
| Multiple Linear Regression | ❌ Not Required |
| Decision Tree              | ❌ Not Required |
| Random Forest              | ❌ Not Required |
| XGBoost                    | ❌ Not Required |
| KNN                        | ✅ Required     |
| K-Means                    | ✅ Required     |
| SVM                        | ✅ Required     |
| PCA                        | ✅ Required     |
| Neural Networks            | ✅ Required     |


If interviewer asks academically

Answer:

To avoid the Dummy Variable Trap, we should drop one dummy variable from each categorical feature. Backward Elimination can then be used to remove statistically insignificant variables based on p-values.

If interviewer asks production ML

Answer:

In modern machine learning using Scikit-Learn, we rarely perform manual Backward Elimination. Instead, we rely on regularization methods such as Lasso, feature importance techniques, or tree-based models. Dummy Variable Trap is less of a concern for predictive modeling because modern libraries can handle redundant features.
